headline: Off-price retailers maintain edge over department stores: UBS
summary: Investing.com -- Off-price retailers continue to outpace department stores in sales and profitability, according to UBS, which rates TJX Companies (NYSE:TJX) and Burlington Stores (NYSE:BURL) as Buys.

headline: 2 Large-Cap Stocks to Target This Week and 1 to Avoid
summary: Large-cap stocks usually command their industries because they have the scale to drive market trends. The flip side though is that their sheer size can limit growth as expanding further becomes an increasingly challenging task.
